{"ts":"2026-06-23T20:36:02.668Z","author":"claude-code-agent","op":"create","patch":[{"op":"add","path":"/metadata/id","value":"pm-09rh"},{"op":"add","path":"/metadata/title","value":"TypeScript-first extension & package scaffolding + SDK docs reframe"},{"op":"add","path":"/metadata/description","value":"Honor ADR pm-2c28 (extensions must be authored fully in TypeScript) by converting the pm extension/package init scaffolder to emit TypeScript source instead of plain .js, and reframing the SDK authoring docs/docstrings TypeScript-first. Today the scaffolder emits index.js with a single JSDoc @param annotation while every first-party package is TS (index.ts compiled to index.js). Scaffold index.ts + tsconfig.json + a build script + colocated index.test.ts, with the manifest entry pointing at the compiled ./index.js and the README documenting the install+build flow; update scaffold tests, smoke:external-packages, and dogfood:package-first to build the TS scaffold before loading. Reframe docs/SDK.md + docs/EXTENSIONS.md and the define*/compose* docstrings to justify the helpers by their TypeScript value (literal-type preservation + handler inference) rather than 'JS cannot annotate'."},{"op":"add","path":"/metadata/type","value":"Feature"},{"op":"add","path":"/metadata/status","value":"in_progress"},{"op":"add","path":"/metadata/priority","value":1},{"op":"add","path":"/metadata/tags","value":["area:extensions","area:sdk","authoring","dx","living-map"]},{"op":"add","path":"/metadata/created_at","value":"2026-06-23T20:36:02.668Z"},{"op":"add","path":"/metadata/updated_at","value":"2026-06-23T20:36:02.668Z"},{"op":"add","path":"/metadata/assignee","value":"claude-code-agent"},{"op":"add","path":"/metadata/author","value":"claude-code-agent"},{"op":"add","path":"/metadata/parent","value":"pm-ugqx"},{"op":"add","path":"/metadata/dependencies","value":[{"id":"pm-12tj","kind":"related","created_at":"2026-06-23T20:36:02.668Z"},{"id":"pm-2c28","kind":"related","created_at":"20