{"ts":"2026-06-23T22:31:52.853Z","author":"codex","op":"comment_add","patch":[{"op":"replace","path":"/metadata/updated_at","value":"2026-06-23T22:31:52.853Z"},{"op":"add","path":"/metadata/comments","value":[{"created_at":"2026-06-23T22:31:52.853Z","author":"codex","text":"Evidence: PR #352 review follow-up implemented. Fixed mergeExtensionBlueprints teardown to run every deactivate in LIFO order and rethrow the first failure; made TypeScript scaffolds compile recursive **/*.ts modules; changed package scaffold .gitignore to root wildcard compiled outputs; added @types/node to standalone README and runtime next-step install commands; hardened dogfood spawnSync failure formatting for null output streams. Verification passed: linked pm test command (4 focused files, 213 tests) passed in PM sandbox; node scripts/run-tests.mjs coverage passed literal 100/100/100/100 (31041 statements, 24166 branches, 5289 functions, 29791 lines; 4987 tests); pnpm release:gates passed after latest source change with the same 100/100/100/100 coverage, npx packed smoke, and dogfood:package-first temp project (88 commands); focused manual temp smoke passed for package init + extension init, recursive subdir helper.ts emitting src/helper.js, wildcard .gitignore, README @types guidance, and next_steps @types guidance; pnpm changelog:pm:check passed with pm-changelog 2026.6.20 and CHANGELOG.md unchanged; pnpm audit reported no vulnerabilities; pnpm outdated only reported @sentry/node 10.59.0 -> 10.60.0, @types/node 20.19.43 -> 26.0.0, commander 14.0.3 -> 15.0.0, not bundled into this review-fix PR due semver/runtime risk; pm package doctor and pm health were ok; pm validate history_drift ok with existing resolution metadata warnings; GH issue #348 remains tracked in pm-2kkl as intermittent Windows nightly worker teardown, while current PR Windows regression checks pass."}]}],"before_hash":"65dfc561a481c9726518a62e29b9d63806ef03b37aba532b9fdd6e6445659d07","after_hash":"b07ea56adb9a5c13802ed460725dab3ae07391fe1b359ae23bf18191ad0e16b7"}
